The paper discusses the use of spatial hierarchies in agent-based models for biological tissue simulation, which involves computational geometry and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software). The paper also involves the implementation of different tree structures, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the simulation, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a likely category. The use of spatial hierarchies also involves computational geometry, which falls under the category of cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper involves the use of data structures for efficient spatial organization, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
